Days after being declared missing, the body of Nigerian student, Obasanjo Adeola Owoyale, has been found in the boot of his car parked in Nicosia schools road, Northern Cyprus. The 33-year old student of the Cyprus International University, left home on July 1, 2019, and was reported missing. The first examination at the scene showed that Owayale had a large wound on his body. His body has been taken to Nicosia Burhan Nalbantoglu State Hospital and the cause of his death will be revealed tomorrow after autopsy. An intensive investigation has also been launched to find out what caused his death. Source